			"content_html": "<p>“What but some profound sense of inadequacy could explain the neediness and the nastiness, the pout and the pettiness, the vanity and the vulgarity, the anger and the aggression?” —<a href=\"https://www.nytimes.com/2017/08/01/opinion/goodbye-anthony-scaramucci.html?smprod=nytcore-ipad&amp;smid=nytcore-ipad-share\">Roger Cohen</a></p>\n",
			"date_published": "2017-08-01T20:16:00-07:00",
			"url": "http://microblog.curtclifton.net/2017/08/01/what-but-some.html"
		},
		
		{
			"id": "http://curt.micro.blog/2017/08/02/and-so-that.html",
	      	
			"content_html": "<p>“And so, that unnerving silence in the face of an erratic executive branch is an abdication, and those in positions of leadership bear particular responsibility.” —<a href=\"http://www.politico.com/magazine/story/2017/07/31/my-party-is-in-denial-about-donald-trump-215442\">Sen. Jeff Flake–R, AZ</a></p>\n",
			"date_published": "2017-08-01T19:00:00-07:00",
			"url": "http://microblog.curtclifton.net/2017/08/01/and-so-that.html"
		},
		
		{
			"id": "http://curt.micro.blog/2017/07/30/the-lesson-that.html",
	      	
			"content_html": "<p>“the lesson that … conservatives appear to be teaching … is that power is more important than principle, … compromise is failure, and … that facts don’t matter.” —<a href=\"https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/grade-point/wp/2017/07/26/its-not-liberals-on-campus-crushing-republican-ideas-its-conservatives/\">Brian C. Rosenberg</a></p>\n",
			"date_published": "2017-07-30T12:44:00-07:00",
			"url": "http://microblog.curtclifton.net/2017/07/30/the-lesson-that.html"
		},
		
		{
			"id": "http://curt.micro.blog/2017/07/30/wealth-it-turns.html",
	      	
			"content_html": "<p>“Wealth, it turns out, leads to behavioral and psychological maladies. The rich act and think in misdirected ways.” —<a href=\"https://www.washingtonpost.com/outlook/being-rich-wrecks-your-soul-we-used-to-know-that/2017/07/28/7d3e2b90-5ab3-11e7-9fc6-c7ef4bc58d13_story.html\">Charles Matthewes and Evan Sandsmark</a></p>\n",
